.TH man 7 "22 May 2016" "1.0" "raytracer man page"
.SH NAME
raytracer - A liblapin raytracing software
.SH SYNOPSIS
raytracer [
.I scene_file.ini
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Il faut mettre la description que l'on souhaite ici
.SH SCENES

[This_is_a_scope]
.br
parameter1=0
.br
parameter2=0.1,0.5,200.0
.br
parameter3="FooFoo", "BarBar"

This is an example of a
.I scope.
Each parameter has 1 or more index.
The data type is not important, but has to be valid.
.br
(ex: if we wait a number,
.B "Hello"
is not valid)


The color parameters use
.I hexadecimal
notation:
.br
0xAABBGGRR or 0xBBGGRR
.br
(A -> Alpha | B -> Blue | G -> Green | R -> Red)

The position/direction parameters are points in space or 3D vectors:
x,y,z
.br
You can either use
.I integer
or
.I floating-point
values.

Rotation has the same notation (x,y,z) but is different:
It's the rotation angle applied on axis x, y, and z for that object, in this precise order.
Those angles are in
.I degree.


The
.B scopes:

[scene]
.br
width=1920
.br
height=1080
.br
background_color=0xFF00AA

If you use this scope, the name should always be "
.I scene
".
The parameters are all optionnals, if you don't use it, default values will be used.


[camera]
.br
position=-5.0,0.1,0.3
.br
direction=0,0,0
.br
focale=0.1
.br
fov=90

If you use this scope, the name should always be "scene".
The parameters are all
.I optionnals
, if you don't use them,
.I default values
will be used.


[mat_glass]
.br
color=0xFF00AA
.br
opacity=0.3
.br
reflectivity=0.4
.br
fresnel=0.8

This is a
.I material.
The name should always begin with "
.I mat_
".
.br
They will be applied on the objects.
Those are visual properties.
You can have more than one material.
.br
The parameters are all
.I optionnals
, if you don't use them,
.I default values
will be used.


[light_1]
.br
type=point
.br
position=0,3,5
.br
color=0xFFFFFF
.br
radius=0.5
.br
power=9.3

[light_2]
.br
type=directionnal
.br
position=0,3,5
.br
direction=3,2.5,1
.br
color=0xFFFF00
.br
power=5

[light_3]
.br
type=spot
.br
position=0,3,5
.br
direction=3,2.5,1
.br
color=0xFF00FF
.br
radius=0.9
.br
power=10

Those are
.I lights.
The name should always begin with "
.I light_
".
.br
You can choose the type between [
.B point
|
.B directionnal
|
.B spot
].
.br
The parameters are all
.I optionnals
, if you don't use them,
.I default values
will be used.


[obj_1]
.br
type=sphere
.br
position=0,0,0
.br
rotation=0,0,0
.br
material=mat_glass
.br
radius=3.0

[obj_002]
.br
type=plane
.br
position=3,0,0
.br
rotation=0,0,30
.br
material=mat_glass
.br
normale=1,0,2

[obj_example]
.br
type=cylinder
.br
position=3,6,0
.br
rotation=20,0,0
.br
material=mat_glass
.br
radius=2.0
.br
height=9

[obj_cone]
.br
type=cone
.br
position=0,2,2
.br
rotation=0,90,0
.br
material=mat_glass
.br
angle=45
.br
height=5

Those are
.I objects.
The name should always begin with "
.I obj_
".
.br
You can choose the type between
.br
[
. B sphere
|
. B plane
|
.B cylinder
|
.B cone
|
.B triangle
|
.B torus
|
.B mobius
|
.B void_cube
|
.B klein
|
.B hyperbola
|
.B ellipsoid
|
.B boy
|
.B cassini
|
.B chair
|
.B kusner
|
.B tritrumpet
|
.B whitney
|
.B tetrahedral
|
.B barth_sextic
|
.B bifolia
|
.B duplin
|
.B cushion
|
.B double_sphere
|
.B tooth
|
.B heart
|
.B hunt
|
.B miter
|
.B kiss
|
.B kummer
|
.B enneper
|
.B bohemian_dome
|
.B bohemian_star
|
.B c8
|
.B chubs
|
.B devil
|
.B quartic_cylinder
|
.B spheroid
|
.B ply
].
.br
You can also choose the material with his
.I scope name.
.br
The parameters are all
.I optionnals
, if you don't use it,
.I default values
will be used.

.SH OBJECTS
Each object has its own
.I parameters.
.br
.B Sphere:
You can specify the
.I radius
of the sphere
.br
.B Plane:
You can specify the
.I normal
vector in
.B x
,
.B y
,
.B z
coordonates.
.br
.B Cylinder:
You can specify the
.I radius
of the cylinder, and also its
.I height
.br
.B Cone:
You can specify the
.I radius
of the cone, and also its
.I height
.br
.B Triangle:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Torus:
You can specify the
.I radius of the hole
(
.B radius_hole
) and the
.I radius of the solid part
(
.B radius_solid
).
.br
.B Mobius:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Void_cube:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Klein:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Hyperbola:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Ellipsoid:
You can specify the
.I height
, the
.I length
and the
.I width
of the ellipsoid.
.br
.B Boy:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Cassini:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Chair:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Kusner:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Tritrumpet:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Whitney:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Tetrahedral:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Barth_sextic:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Bifolia:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Duplin:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Cushion:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Double Sphere:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Tooth:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Heart:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Hunt:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Miter:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Kiss:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Kummer:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Enneper:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Bohemian Dome:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Bohemian Star:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B C8:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Chubs:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Devil:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Quartic Cylinder:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Spheroid:
No specific parameters.
.br
.B Ply:
You can specify the path (
.I file="path/file.ply"
) of the file you want to load.

.SH CONFIG
The
.I config.ini
file contains
.I general
configuration, such as
.I network
settings or
.I effects
settings.
.br

The
.B [network]
scope contains the
.I port
and the number of
.I max_client
that the server should accept.
.br

The
.B [effect]
scope contains the effect
.I type
and its
.I parameters.
Please, refer to the
.I post-render effect section
of the man to get more informations about this.

Here is an exemple of correct config.ini.


[network]
.br
port=12345
.br
max_client=0
.br

[effect]
.br
type=contrast
.br
value=142

.SH POST-RENDER EFFECTS
The possible post-render effects are
.br
[
.B black_and_white
|
.B pastel
|
.B negative
|
.B bayer
|
.B sepia
|
.B eight_bit
|
.B max_filter
|
.B retro
|
.B watercolor
|
.B solarized
|
.B rotate
|
.B contrast
]
.br
Here are the possible parameters for the various effects, if an effect is not listed here it means it has no parameters:


.B rotate :
.br
angle_r=
.br
angle_g=
.br
angle_b=
.br
The value of these parameters should be an angle in degree.

.B solarized :
.br
max_r=
.br
max_g=
.br
max_b=
.br
The value of these parameters should be the pixel cap.


.B contrast :
.br
value=
.br
The value should be the contrast value. A higher value will give you a higher contrast.

If one of those parameters is missing, a default value will replace it.

.SH SCRIPTS
.B before_expand.sh
script replaces all the
.I x
,
.I y
and
.I z
in an equation by, respectivly,
.I (a+k*t)
,
.I (b+l*t)
and
.I (z+m*t)

Once you developped your expression, you can turn it into a polynomial equation thanks to
.B toto.sh
, which will look like this :

.I A
* x^4 +
.I B
* x^3 +
.I C
* x^2 +
.I D
* x +
.I E
= 0

The script's output starts with
.I E
and ends with
.I A

